-- Mozambique Rainfall Causes Crop Losses in Zambezi Valley, Noticias Reports
-- Fred Katerere
-- 2010-07-15T01:04:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/mozambique-rainfall-causes-crop-losses-in-zambezi-valley-noticias-reports.html

          
          
             Intensive rain and increased
discharge from the Cahora Bassa hydroelectric damn in central
Mozambique has resulted in crop losses along the Zambezi river
valley, state-controlled Noticias reported, citing Adelina
Randinho, an administrative officer for the Caia district.  
 She didnâ€™t provide figures for the amount of crops lost,
Noticias said. Randinho said the rains along the valley are
worsening, according to the report.  
